  • Zielgre: Wohlstand
    • BIP
    • Alternative Wohlstandsmae?
  • Variablen zur Analyse von Wohlstand
    • Inflationsrate:
      • AD-AS-Modell (statisch & dynamisch)
    • Zinsen:
      • Mittlere Frist (kleine/groe & geschlossene/offene Volkswirtschaft)
      • IS-LM Modell (kleine/groe & geschlossene Volkswirtschaft)
      • Mundell-Flemming Modell (groe & offene Volkswirtschaft)
    • Wechselkurse:
      • Mittlere Frist (kleine/groe & offene Volkswirtschaft)
      • Mundell-Flemming Modell (kleine/groe & offene Volkswirtschaft)

# fredr_set_key("... insert-your-personal-key-here ...")
# See: https://rpubs.com/FSl/609471
add_rec_shade <- function(st_date,ed_date,shade_color="darkgray",zoo.mon=FALSE,zoo.qtr=FALSE) {
  
  library(fredr)
  library(ecm)
  library(ggplot2)
  library(zoo)
  #fredr_set_key("insert_your_api_key")
  
  #st_date<-as.Date("2001-06-01")
  #ed_date<-as.Date(Sys.Date())
  
  recession <- fredr(series_id = "USRECD",observation_start = as.Date(st_date),observation_end = as.Date(ed_date))
  
  recession$diff <- recession$value-lagpad(recession$value,k=1)
  recession <- recession[!is.na(recession$diff),]
  recession.start <- recession[recession$diff==1,]$date
  recession.end <- recession[recession$diff==(-1),]$date
  
  if(length(recession.start)>length(recession.end)){
    recession.end <-c (recession.end,Sys.Date())
  }
  if(length(recession.end)>length(recession.start)){
    recession.start <- c(min(recession$date),recession.start)
  }
  
  recs <- as.data.frame(cbind(recession.start,recession.end))
  recs$recession.start <- as.Date(as.numeric(recs$recession.start),origin=as.Date("1970-01-01"))
  if(zoo.mon==TRUE){
    recs$recession.start <- as.yearmon(recs$recession.start,"%b%y")
  }
  if(zoo.qtr==TRUE){
    recs$recession.start <- as.yearqtr(recs$recession.start,"%y-Q%q")
  }
  
  recs$recession.end <- as.Date(recs$recession.end,origin=as.Date("1970-01-01"))
  if(zoo.mon==TRUE){
    recs$recession.end <- as.yearmon(recs$recession.end,"%b%y")
  }
  if(zoo.qtr==TRUE){
    recs$recession.end <- as.yearqtr(recs$recession.end,"%y-Q%q")
  }
  
  if(nrow(recs)>0){
    rec_shade <- geom_rect(data=recs, inherit.aes=F, 
                           aes(xmin=recession.start, xmax=recession.end, ymin=-Inf, ymax=+Inf), 
                           fill=shade_color, alpha=0.5)
    return(rec_shade)
  }
}

# Meta data
met.dat <- fredr_series_search_text("GDPC1")
# Data
ser.dat <- fredr_series_observations(series_id=met.dat$id[1],
                                     observation_start=as.Date("1947-01-01"),
                                     units="lin")
# Transform date to yearmon class
ser.dat$date.zoo <- as.yearqtr(ser.dat$date,"%y-Q%q")
# Construct plot
gdp.01.plot <- ggplot(data=ser.dat,mapping=aes(x=date.zoo,y=value,color=series_id)) +
  add_rec_shade(min(ser.dat$date),max(ser.dat$date),zoo.mon=TRUE,zoo.qtr=FALSE) +
  geom_line(color = "black", size = 1) +
  scale_y_continuous(name="Billions of Chained 2012 Dollars",labels=comma) +
  scale_x_yearqtr(breaks=seq(from=min(ser.dat$date.zoo),to=max(ser.dat$date.zoo),by=8),
                  minor_breaks=seq(from=min(ser.dat$date.zoo),to=max(ser.dat$date.zoo),by=4),
                  format="%Y-Q%q",
                  expand = c(0, 0)) +
  labs(title = met.dat$title[1],
       caption = "Source: U.S. Bureau of Economic Analysis", 
       x = "", y = "Billions of Chained 2012 Dollars") +
  theme(legend.position="none",
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, vjust = 0.5),
        text = element_text(size = 20))

Main Refinancing Operation (MRO) rate 

# Main refinancing operations (fixed rate)
filter <- list(startPeriod = 1999-01-01,
               endPeriod = 2022-01-01)
key <- "FM.B.U2.EUR.4F.KR.MRR_FR.LEV"
dat.01 <- get_data(key, filter)
dat.01$date <- as.Date(dat.01$obstime)
colnames(dat.01)[9] <- c("mro.01.00")
# Main refinancing operations (minimun bid rate)
filter <- list(startPeriod = 1999-01-01,
               endPeriod = 2022-01-01)
key <- "FM.B.U2.EUR.4F.KR.MRR_MBR.LEV"
dat.02 <- get_data(key, filter)
dat.02$date <- as.Date(dat.02$obstime)
colnames(dat.02)[9] <- c("mro.02.00")

# head(dat.01$date) # only changes are recorded

date.df <- data.frame(date=seq(as.Date("1999-01-01"), as.Date("2022-01-31"), by="day")) 

# insert all dates for fixed rate
dat.03 <- merge(date.df,dat.01,by="date",all.x = TRUE)
dat.03$mro.01[1] <- dat.03$mro.01.00[1]
for (ii in 2:nrow(dat.03)) {
  if (is.na(dat.03$mro.01.00[ii])) {
    dat.03$mro.01[ii] <- dat.03$mro.01[ii-1]
  } else {
    dat.03$mro.01[ii] <- dat.03$mro.01.00[ii]
  }
}

# insert all dates for minimum bid rate
dat.04 <- merge(date.df,dat.02,by="date",all.x = TRUE)
dat.04$mro.02[1] <- dat.04$mro.02.00[1]
for (ii in 2:nrow(dat.04)) {
  if (is.na(dat.04$mro.02.00[ii])) {
    dat.04$mro.02[ii] <- dat.04$mro.02[ii-1]
  } else {
    dat.04$mro.02[ii] <- dat.04$mro.02.00[ii]
  }
}

# mro as combination of fixed rate and minimum bid rate
dat.05 <- data.frame(date=dat.03$date,
                     mro=ifelse(dat.03$date %in% seq(as.Date("2000-06-28"), as.Date("2008-10-15"), by="day"),dat.04$mro.02,dat.03$mro.01))

# Construct plot
plt <- ggplot(data=dat.05,mapping=aes(x=date,y=mro)) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  scale_y_continuous(name="Percent",labels=comma) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "2 years",
               date_minor_breaks = "1 years",
               date_labels = "%Y",
               expand = c(0, 0)) +
  labs(title = "ECB Main Refinancing Operations",
       caption = "Source: ECB", 
       x = "", y = "Percent") +
  theme(legend.position="bottom",
        axis.text.x = element_text(vjust = 0.5),
        text = element_text(size = 20))
# Print plot
